<b>Recovery:</b> SCP-ES-100 came to the attention of the Foundation on 07/14/2007, after an emergency call was made to the online maintenance and breakdown services of the ████████ company by PoI-034.3701/ES-100 from, it is assumed, the interior of a Model 2800 elevator located in the city of Valencia, Spain.<br><br>

The subsequent investigation showed that the ████████ company was unaware of the anomalous effects produced by SCP-ES-100 in its Model 2800 elevators, which led to ruling out that the anomaly was intentionally introduced into its design. As a preventive measure, the production of Model 2800 elevators was suspended under the pretext of serious safety errors.<br><br>

Foundation personnel requisitioned all Model 2800 cabins in service, mainly in the Iberian Peninsula and most of the countries that make up Latin America. They were replaced by Model 3100 elevators under the justification of a free joint urban renewal plan by the ████████ company and the state institutions of each region.<br><br>

<div class="square"><b>Update - 02/14/2008:</b> Despite the fact that the last of the Model 2800 elevators present in the official inventory of the ████████ company was withdrawn from circulation on 02/13/2008, it has been determined that an unknown number have not yet been acquired by the Foundation. It is believed that these are in public circulation, possible due to their illegal second-hand sale and altered serial numbers.<br><br>

Given the potential risk this presents to the population, staff members of Mobile Task Force Sigma-22 ("Prey Dogs") currently maintain low priority active tracking for new instances of Model 2800 elevators that still remain outside containment.</div><br>

